  "market_context": "ETH was trading higher with a bullish structural bias, but price ran into the previous day high and a prior swing high, creating a conflicted bias. The hourly was forming a reversal off these highs while respecting up-close candles, with surrounding price action characterized by failure swings and a large existing range.",
  "key_observation": "An hourly sweep and closure back inside off the previous day high, paired with a 5-minute change in state of delivery through the up-close candle series, defined a t-spot where a 1-minute inversion could be used as a precision entry for the bearish expansion.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify conflicted bias: bullish structure but price has swept the prior swing high and previous day high, prompting use of the daily profile.",
    "On the hourly, recognize a reversal forming off previous day high with failure swings to the left as downside targets, and note the large existing range suggests no further large upside wick is expected.",
    "Confirm the hourly sweep and closure back inside the previous candle, establishing bearish hourly bias.",
    "Drop to the 5-minute and wait for a change in state of delivery — a close through the series of down-close (up-close) candles that swept the low/high — to align the 5M with the hourly.",
    "After 5M alignment is confirmed on the next candle, mark out the t-spot where the higher-timeframe wick is expected to form, anchored to the order block / fair value gap.",
    "When price retraces into the t-spot and forms the hourly wick, drop to the 1-minute and look for an inversion — wait for a 1-minute close above the inversion level.",
    "Enter short on the 1-minute inversion close with stop placed at the swing high, targeting a minimum of 2R with optional runners held to an 11:00 time-based exit toward the daily open / failure swing liquidity."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached the 2R target, with price trading through the failure swings to the downside; runners could be held to an 11:00 time-based exit on the expansion candle close.",
  "lessons": "Aligning hourly sweep-and-close with a 5-minute change in state of delivery defines a high-probability t-spot. Using a 1-minute inversion inside the t-spot allows entry on side with the wick, giving a tight invalidation and 2R+ potential on the higher-timeframe expansion.",
